Italian Watchdog Tightens Company Disclosure Rules, FT Reports

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-02-25T01:47:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/italian-watchdog-tightens-company-disclosure-rules-ft-reports.html
Consob, the Italian stock-market
regulator, has written new rules requiring companies to disclose
more information on executive pay and succession planning, the
Financial Times reported, citing a statement from the regulator.  Italian companies will have to detail separately the types
of payments received by senior executives, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in  London  at 
 jjordan22@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 